Secondary New Hire Candidate Interview Questions   *** for dufferin  peel catholic district school board

1. Catholicity

In Dufferin-Peel, we are looking for Catholic educational leaders who create and sustain a Catholic learning environment. One of the shared priorities articulated within
the Catholic Board Improvement Learning Cycle being:

"We are called to affirm our Catholic Faith, in word and action and in all that we do.

" How will you instill, integrate and demonstrate our Catholic faith in the classroom and the school community? Demonstrate with detailed evidence from your practice and 
experience.

2. Professional Knowledge

Teachers are expected to use their professional knowledge of curriculum and teaching practices to promote the learning and achievement of their pupils in our Catholic schools.


Referencing your unit outline, describe the process for planning your unit. Detail how you incorporated:

Ontario curriculum                                          Assessments

Ministry/Board expected practice                            Evaluation

Unit organization and components                            Literacy/Numeracy



3. Professional Practice

Within Catholic schools the Catholic Graduate Expectations provide all those involved in Catholic education both a vision and a practical tool to ensure that the treasures of our Catholic faith and tradition properly inspire all that we do in our schools.

Referencing your unit outline, describe how you incorporate the assigned Catholic Graduate Expectation in your pedagogy as well as its impact on the classroom environment.

                                OVERALL EXPECTATION                              SPECIFIC EXPECTATION
Assigned
CGE:                           An Effective Communicator Who:              Uses and integrates the Catholic faith tradition, in the critical analysis of the arts, media,
                                                                             technology and information systems to enhance the quality of life.



4)Commitment to Pupils and Pupil Learning

Teachers use effective classroom management techniques to promote the learning and achievement of their students in our Catholic schools. Commitment to the well-being and 
development of all pupils is the foundation of teaching practice in our Catholic schools.

Part A: At the beginning of a new semester what structures and processes do you establish to create a safe, caring and inclusive classroom environment to meet the diverse
needs of all learners in your classroom?

Part B: Even within a safe, caring, and inclusive classroom environment, classroom management challenges arise. Describe vour process for addressina these issues.



5. Commitment to Pupil and Professional Development

Contribution to the well-being and development of students beyond the classroom is essential to the life of a

Catholic school.

Part A: Explain the benefits of engaging in a strong co-curricular program in a school.

Part B: identify interests, skills and/or certifications you possess that will enable you to contribute to the co-curricular life of the school.

